<TITLE> BCL violence shuts Barisal medical college </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Barisal, Apr 17 (bdnews24.com) Barisal Sher-e-Bangla Medical College closed indefinitely early Friday after a spate of overnight clashes between supporters of pro-Awami League Bangladesh Chhatra League (BCL) that left at least 10 injured and a student abducted. The students vacated their halls by 8am on orders from the authorities. "The academic council decided at 12:30am to close the college indefinitely due to students' clashes," acting principal of the college Abu Taher told bdnews24.com. Violence erupted late Thursday night between two groups of the college unit of BCL at Jamilur Rahman Hall. Several rooms were vandalised during the fighting over control of the campus. It later spread to other halls. MBBS students of Batch-35 and 37--Didar, Saif, Tanvir, and Al-Mamun and Mehedi, respectively, were injured in the clashes. Assistant police commissioner of Barisal Metropolitan Police Hayatul Islam told bdnews24.com that a general diary was filed with Kotwali Police Station. The diary alleged that MBBS student Rabiul Islam of Batch-37 had been abducted . Police could not rescue the student until Friday morning. Additional police were deployed on the campus. bdnews
